                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d604">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.4016/158: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-17T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 17, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 17—8:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>92. My telegrams numbers 83, March 10, 7 p.m., and 89, March 15, 6 p.m. Ciano
                    assured me definitely today that his statement to me on March 10 held good so
                    far as concerns the time permitted foreign Jews to leave Italy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
